# Trivy suppressions for the worker image gate (sandbox-security.yml).
# Scope: Debian bookworm OS libraries pulled in by the base image and the git
# runtime dependency. Every entry below is a CVE for which Debian ships no fix
# (status affected / fix_deferred / will_not_fix at scan time, 2026-07-21).
# Node.js application and npm-bundled dependencies are NOT suppressed here —
# those must be patched by upgrading the package, and any new CVE with an
# available fix will still fail the gate.

# util-linux / core system libraries (no Debian fix available)
CVE-2026-53615
CVE-2026-41992
CVE-2026-54369
# curl / ssh2 / ldap used by git for HTTPS transport (no Debian fix available)
CVE-2026-12064
CVE-2026-6276
CVE-2026-8286
CVE-2026-8927
CVE-2026-8932
CVE-2023-2953
CVE-2026-55199
CVE-2026-55200
CVE-2026-7598
# expat / ncurses runtime libraries (no Debian fix available)
CVE-2025-59375
CVE-2026-25210
CVE-2026-45186
CVE-2026-56131
CVE-2026-56407
CVE-2026-56408
CVE-2025-69720
# perl 5.36 pulled by git (no Debian fix available)
CVE-2026-13221
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-57432
CVE-2026-9538
# zlib 1.2.13 in zip64 writing path; Debian marked will_not_fix. The worker
# never writes zip archives; the vulnerable code path is not exercised.
CVE-2023-45853
